<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="184" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1248½</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to President <persName corresp="#p_HH1" type="to">Hoover</persName>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-06">July 6,
                                    1932</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. President</hi>: I am sending you
                                herewith a stenographic record of my talk yesterday with <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Norman Davis</persName>,<note n="31" xml:id="d184fn31">See memorandum of conversation, <ref target="#pg_263">p. 263</ref>.</note> which I summarized to
                                you at Cabinet Meeting. It is so interesting that I thought you
                                would like to read it in full. As you will see, there is still a
                                possibility of something unpleasant coming out either in the House
                                of Commons or in <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName>’s
                                speech; but in general what was a very awkward matter is smoothing
                                down into pretty good shape.</p>
                            <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry L. Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>